Actress Mary Njoku has sternly warned ‘age-shamers’ to desist or face the unsolicited consequence. The Director General of ROK Studios in an Instagram post challenged the supposedly young individuals involved in the act of age-shaming others to opt for the option of dying young if aging feels ugly to them. “Dear Nigerians, there is nothing like age-shaming.   Many unsuccessful years behind every successful man, not…     Fave takes over from Asa as Spotify Equal Music ambassador     Oshara releases new single   “If you feel getting old is an ugly thing try dying young. “Any small thing ‘old woman! Go and get married. Your mate dey husband house old cargo. See this mumu old man’ “Unfortunately for you, you are speaking to your future self, that’s if you are lucky to live that long.” She added: “Stop AGE-SHAMING people if you don’t want the angel of de4th to grant your personal wish of not getting old!!! “Aging is inevitable! Embrace it!!”